notmuch-address-cache(1)                              notmuch-address-cache(1)



NNAAMMEE
       notmuch-address-cache  -  caches  the  result  from notmuch-address and
       search within this cached version.


SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
       nnoottmmuucchh--aaddddrreessss--ccaacchhee [ _C_O_M_M_A_N_D ] [ _A_R_G ]


DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       nnoottmmuucchh--aaddddrreessss--ccaacchhee is basically a cache in  front  of  the  _n_o_t_m_u_c_h_-
       _a_d_d_r_e_s_s command.

       notmuch-address-cache caches all sender and recipients you communicated
       with.


CCoommmmaannddss
       hheellpp, ----hheellpp, --hh
              Show help text.

       vveerrssiioonn, ----vveerrssiioonn, --vv
              Show the version.

       rreebbuuiilldd, ----rreebbuuiilldd, --rr [----jjssoonn | ----tteexxtt]
              Uses _n_o_t_m_u_c_h_-_a_d_d_r_e_s_s to find all sender/recipient  you  communi-
              cated  with  and  print them out to the file _~_/_._n_o_t_m_u_c_h_-_a_d_d_r_e_s_s_-
              _c_a_c_h_e_/_a_d_d_r_e_s_s_e_s. The format of the cached addresses  are  stored
              in  json, if you rebuild your cache with option ----jjssoonn. The for-
              mat of the cached addresses are stored in text, if  you  rebuild
              your  cache with option----tteexxtt. Format text is recommended if you
              want to query the cache with mmuutttt. Format json is recommended if
              you want to query the cache with aalloott.

       uuppddaattee, ----uuppddaattee, --uu [----jjssoonn | ----tteexxtt]
              Uses  _n_o_t_m_u_c_h_-_a_d_d_r_e_s_s to find all sender/recipient, based on the
              ttaagg::nneeww, you communicated with and prepend them out to the  file
              _~_/_._n_o_t_m_u_c_h_-_a_d_d_r_e_s_s_-_c_a_c_h_e_/_a_d_d_r_e_s_s_e_s.  It  expect  the notmuch tag
              ttaagg::nneeww on all messages to extract  the  sender  and  recipients
              from  there.  You  can configure notmuch to apply the ttaagg::nneeww to
              all messages. This is  basically  done  if  you  edit  the  file
              _~_/_._n_o_t_m_u_c_h_-_c_o_n_f_i_g,  go  into section [new] and add the value nneeww
              to  the  key  ttaaggss.  For  more  details   see   https://notmuch-
              mail.org/initial_tagging/ in section 'The _n_e_w tag approach'. The
              format of the cached addresses are stored in json, if you update
              your  cache  with  option  ----jjssoonn.  The  format  of  the  cached
              addresses are stored in text, if  you  update  your  cache  with
              option ----tteexxtt.

       qquueerryy, ----qquueerryy, --qq
              Greps the cache file for the given query. Interpret the query as
              an extended regular expression. Perform case  insesitive  match-
              ing.


EExxaammppllee WWoorrkkffllooww
       Setup  notmuch  to  use  'The  _n_e_w  tag approach'. See https://notmuch-
       mail.org/initial_tagging/.

       mmuutttt - Using mutt as mua
              Rebuild your cache by  Executing  nnoottmmuucchh--aaddddrreessss--ccaacchhee  rreebbuuiilldd
              ----tteexxtt.  Edit  your  _._m_u_t_t_r_c  file and add the query command sseett
              qquueerryy__ccoommmmaanndd == ""nnoottmmuucchh--aaddddrreessss--ccaacchhee qquueerryy ''%%ss''"".

       aalloott - Using alot as mua
              Rebuild your cache by  Executing  nnoottmmuucchh--aaddddrreessss--ccaacchhee  rreebbuuiilldd
              ----jjssoonn.  Edit  your  _._c_o_n_f_i_g_/_a_l_o_t_/_c_o_n_f_i_g  file and add the query
              command under the _a_b_o_o_k section.   ccoommmmaanndd  ==  ''nnoottmmuucchh--aaddddrreessss--
              ccaacchhee qquueerryy''.

              [accounts]
                [[youraccount]]
                  [[abook]]
                    type = shellcommand
                    command = 'notmuch-address-cache query'
                    regexp    =    '\[?{"name":   "(?P<name>.*)",   "address":
              "(?P<email>.+)", "name-addr": ".*"}[,\]]?'
                    shellcommand_external_filtering = False





